@minggo 
I suggest only leave one API for read raw data, such as:

```
std::string FileUtils::getFileData(const std::string& filename)
{
    std::string s;
    getContents(filename, &s);
    return s;
}
```

Remark: The 'std::string' is not just string, Actual it can handle binary or null-terminated-string.
So, at least, for engine, We can replace every raw read APIs with this API.

The following is the source code of `ParticleSystem::initWithFile`:

``` c++
bool ParticleSystem::initWithFile(const std::string& plistFile)
{
    bool ret = false;
    _plistFile = FileUtils::getInstance()->fullPathForFilename(plistFile);
    ValueMap dict = FileUtils::getInstance()->getValueMapFromFile(_plistFile);

    CCASSERT( !dict.empty(), "Particles: file not found");

    // FIXME: compute path from a path, should define a function somewhere to do it
    string listFilePath = plistFile;
    if (listFilePath.find('/') != string::npos)
    {
        listFilePath = listFilePath.substr(0, listFilePath.rfind('/') + 1);
        ret = this->initWithDictionary(dict, listFilePath);
    }
    else
    {
        ret = this->initWithDictionary(dict, "");
    }

    return ret;
}
```

The application will crash, when the particle file doesn't exist.
It should return false instead of crash the application. We should never assume that a file will always exists.

